{"title":"The world of labor shortages, the culture that is alcohol","link":"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/895210643/0/marginalrevolution~The-world-of-labor-shortages-the-culture-that-is-alcohol.html","date":1714755263000,"content":"<blockquote>\r\n<p>Drunken-driving deaths in the U.S. have risen to levels not seen in nearly two decades, federal data show, a major setback to long-running road-safety efforts.</p>\r\n<p>At the same time, arrests for driving under the influence have plummeted, as police grapple with challenges like hiring woes and heightened concern around traffic stops.</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<p>Here is <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://www.wsj.com/us-news/drunk-driving-deaths-rise-dui-arrests-down-92d53ea7\" target=\"_blank\">more from the WSJ</a>.  “About 13,500 people died in alcohol-impairment crashes in 2022…”  Here is <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://marginalrevolution.com/marginalrevolution/2013/04/the-culture-of-guns-the-culture-of-alcohol.html\" target=\"_blank\">my earlier post</a> on the culture of guns and the cultural of alcohol.</p>\r\n<p>Via the excellent <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://www.nationalaffairs.com/blog/detail/findings-a-daily-roundup/open-to-interpretation\" target=\"_blank\">Kevin Lewis</a>.</p>\r\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://marginalrevolution.com/marginalrevolution/2024/05/the-world-of-labor-shortages-the-culture-that-is-alcohol.html\">The world of labor shortages, the culture that is alcohol</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://marginalrevolution.com\">Marginal REVOLUTION</a>.</p>\r\n<img height=\"1\" width=\"1\" src=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/i/895210643/0/marginalrevolution\" />\r\n<div><a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/28/895210643/marginalrevolution\"><img height=\"20\